## Purpose

This notebook handles all global configuration and package management for the
ACD-GARCH pipeline. It must be run (or sourced) before any subsequent notebook.

- **Inputs:** none
- **Outputs:** none (environment configuration only)

---

## 1. Global Options

```{r global-options, include=FALSE}

# Fixed CRAN mirror: ensures consistent package resolution when knitting
# non-interactively or in CI environments
options(repos = c(CRAN = "https://cloud.r-project.org"))

# Prevent automatic coercion of character columns to factors.
# Critical for timestamp and symbol columns — silent factor coercion
# produces nonsensical results in data.table joins and lubridate parsing.
options(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Timezone: all raw tick timestamps are labelled Europe/London (BST/GMT switching).
# Setting TZ globally ensures lubridate and data.table parse consistently
# across the full April–June 2020 period, which spans the BST transition.
# Do not change this — timezone misalignment in tick data produces silent
# duration calculation errors that are extremely difficult to detect downstream.
Sys.setenv(TZ = "Europe/London")

# Reproducibility seed.
# ACD and GARCH estimation are deterministic (pure MLE), so results are
# seed-independent. The seed is set here to cover any bootstrap diagnostics
# or simulation steps that may be introduced in later notebooks.
set.seed(2024)

# Default chunk behaviour for all notebooks in this project.
knitr::opts_chunk$set(
  echo       = TRUE,   # always show code in rendered output
  message    = FALSE,  # suppress package load messages
  warning    = FALSE,  # suppress warnings (review manually during development)
  fig.width  = 9,      # consistent plot width across all notebooks
  fig.height = 5       # consistent plot height across all notebooks
)
```

